Governor E.S.L. Narasimhan will examine the works of Mission Bhageeratha, the drinking water grid project taken up by the State government, at three places in Medak, Warangal and Nalgonda districts on Wednesday. According to officials, he will examine the works at Gajwel, Janagaon and Yadagirigutta areas of the three districts by taking off in a helicopter at 10.30 a.m. from here. The government has plans to supply drinking water from April 30 to the areas to be visited by the Governor on Wednesday.In all, the government is planning to supply water through the project in 10 constituencies â€“ Medchal in Ranga Reddy district, Gajwel, Siddipet and Dubbak in Medak, Janagaon, Station Ghanpur and Palakurthy in Warangal and Aler, Bhongir and Thungathurthi in Nalgonda district from April 30.